Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.80,0:01:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, please escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.77,0:01:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre, I am escaping.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.94,0:01:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not putting up a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.57,0:01:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This fight will never end,\Nso I've opted to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.74,0:01:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If I should die, then so be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.74,0:01:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not so attached to space\Nthat I'll compromise myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.85,0:01:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,FATHER!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.00,0:01:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.06,0:02:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,FATHER!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.29,0:02:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's huge...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.59,0:02:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what kind of person\Nthis goodwill ambassador is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.52,0:02:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.76,0:02:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That mobile suit was used\Nagainst OZ on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.43,0:02:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll check it, for security.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The new system since OZ and\Nthe colonies became united...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.89,0:02:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,...has had a considerable\Ninfluence on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.32,0:02:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,On behalf of my nation...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.06,0:03:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,...I've come to find out\Nabout this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.66,0:03:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Your nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.06,0:03:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.43,0:03:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come here from the\NSanc Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.30,0:03:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Milliardo Peacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.03,0:03:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, His Excellency has had\Nties with the Sanc Kingdom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.50,0:03:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,...since his youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.14,0:03:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard your nation was\Nrecovering from the wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.21,0:03:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I understand\Nthe implications of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.31,0:03:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought I could\Ngive advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.92,0:03:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,...to the colonies desiring\Nmilitary power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.42,0:03:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many ways\Nto obtain peace for oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.06,0:03:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Between us, we'll find\Nthe best direction to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then will you allow me\Nto act on my own accord...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.33,0:03:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...while I'm here in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.50,0:03:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.93,0:03:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be on the\Nright track to peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.13,0:03:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...Representative Lady Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Peacecraft, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He's none other than that\NOZ traitor, Zechs Merquise!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.58,0:03:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Space Colony D 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.41,0:03:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the United Earth Sphere\NAlliance command station...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.18,0:03:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,...is located.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.55,0:04:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ wasn't controlling\Nthe colonies by force...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.39,0:04:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,...but recommending they join\Na nation of the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.99,0:04:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,D 120 continued in its function\Nas Earth's voice in outer space...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.16,0:04:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,...not forgoing its position as\Na military institute from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.60,0:04:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of the Alliance Space Force\NCommander General Septem...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.87,0:04:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,...Gwinter was the colony's\Nrepresentative.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The former Alliance members\Nassociated with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.48,0:04:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,...had been troubled by the\Ncolonial independence policy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.78,0:04:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...backed by OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.85,0:04:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you hesitating for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.88,0:04:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ is trying to secure even\Nmore power for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.35,0:04:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We must stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.95,0:04:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Technological strength will just\Nbecome a threat to the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ thinks of space as merely\Na factory for military supplies!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Only we can stop them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.50,0:04:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our mission!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.77,0:04:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A battle will result in\Nmany casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.00,0:04:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With our military strength,\Ndialog is still an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.11,0:04:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They're planning to use\Nouter space...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.07,0:04:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,...to develop and manufacture\Nmobile dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.18,0:05:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,These murder weapons\Nwill allow OZ...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.81,0:05:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,...to take over and\Ndictate the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.08,0:05:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Does everybody feel the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.55,0:05:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs Merquise has arrived\Nin space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lightning Count is alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.89,0:05:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Earth that fears increased\Narms in space the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.46,0:05:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs knows OZ well and\Nhe wishes for peace on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.60,0:05:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We should take some time\Nto hear what he has to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.57,0:05:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs has nothing to do\Nwith OZ anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.11,0:05:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What's he doing in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That man holds a great\Naffection for his homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.31,0:05:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew someone had\Nto take action.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.65,0:05:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though it was risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.38,0:05:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This visit holds significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Very nicely done,\NTreize Khushrenada!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.79,0:05:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in space are\Nclose to accepting OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.39,0:05:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.76,0:05:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And Colonel Une's achievements\Nhave been impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.76,0:05:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She's forming friendly relations\Nwith one colony after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.86,0:05:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of independence\Nbuilt by forming a nation...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,...will trigger a desire for\Nproductivity and defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.77,0:06:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This leads to the nation\Nbecoming militaristic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.31,0:06:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means that every\Ncountry on the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.68,0:06:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,...will jump into OZ's arms\Nand beg to be governed by us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.95,0:06:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful, Treize.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You've made space a member\Nof the Romefeller Foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.78,0:06:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.48,0:06:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mr. Tubarov; have you\Nfinished packing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.09,0:06:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.79,0:06:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Tubarov is heading for\Nouter space to oversee...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.46,0:06:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,...mobile doll production and\Nstrengthen our military force.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.76,0:06:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une has readily accepted\Nthe new addition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.26,0:06:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une did?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.03,0:06:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Une seems to be very\Npleased with the mobile dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.84,0:06:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your Excellency, it's been{\i0}\N{\i1}a long time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.31,0:06:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's Lady Une.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.58,0:06:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.21,0:06:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was sure you'd be coming{\i0}\N{\i1}with Chief Engineer Tubarov.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.59,0:06:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to talk about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.22,0:06:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you plan to utilize\Nthe mobile dolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.42,0:06:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll use them as your soldiers{\i0}\N{\i1}so you won't need to suffer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:06:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My soldiers?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.73,0:07:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not being fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.77,0:07:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who must\Nlead the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.87,0:07:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But you've simply left the\Nworld in a state of confusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.51,0:07:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here to be of some\Nassistance to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.48,0:07:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've also laid out\Na new future for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.18,0:07:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Wars will never disappear\Nfrom the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore the strongest\Nshould rule the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.72,0:07:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People even take pleasure in\Nbeing controlled by the strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.03,0:07:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's merely natural for the\Nworld to continue fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.66,0:07:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But that encourages\Nmeaningless bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.40,0:07:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You're capable of loving\Nall people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.54,0:07:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a heart that\Ncan make you a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.20,0:07:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,From outer space, you can\Ncreate peace on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.08,0:07:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.28,0:07:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These are your ideals\Nfor the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.25,0:07:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's what you wanted,{\i0}\N{\i1}Your Excellency.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.62,0:07:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My ideal is merely the\Nfantasy of one individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.95,0:07:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,History is an accumulation\Nof daily events.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.86,0:08:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no interest in\Nan individual's future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.29,0:08:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your future's already{\i0}\N{\i1}been determined.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.80,0:08:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your future's destined to be{\i0}\N{\i1}in outer space.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.07,0:08:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.93,0:08:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not that strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.44,0:08:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs and the Gundam pilots\Nare making an effort...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.01,0:08:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,...to construct a new future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.21,0:08:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.08,0:08:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,History will repeat itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.11,0:08:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lady Une that I was\Nso fond of.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.06,0:08:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.29,0:08:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Zechs Merquise, for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So Zechs is in space?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He's establishing relations...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.63,0:08:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...with the Alliance's\NMilitary Colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Lieutenant Nichol.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.13,0:08:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Destroy the Alliance's{\i0}\N{\i1}Space Force.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.54,0:08:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's no reason to leave{\i0}\N{\i1}them roaming about...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.57,0:08:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...now that the mobile dolls{\i0}\N{\i1}have been completed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.04,0:08:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've also sent Colonel Une{\i0}\N{\i1}orders for the near future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.48,0:08:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tell her I want her comments.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.95,0:08:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.82,0:09:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.92,0:09:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We were enemies at one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.16,0:09:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But changes in wartime bring\Nchanges in relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.26,0:09:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I care about the Earth,\Njust as the Alliance does.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.17,0:09:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you came from Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.30,0:09:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,...to discuss the current arms\Nissue of the Space Colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.31,0:09:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If this simply involved a new\Nmilitary nation being formed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.84,0:09:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...then I wouldn't be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.68,0:09:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if they're being\Ntricked by OZ...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.55,0:09:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,...then I can't ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.28,0:09:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ is planning to use space\Nas its military factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.19,0:09:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That would result in even more\Nsevere disputes on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.36,0:09:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...and serious casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel about the\Npeople in space, Mr. Peacecraft?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.63,0:09:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Teachings of the great leader,\Nthe late Heero Yuy, still exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.33,0:09:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Outer space once thrived\Nas a world...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.74,0:09:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,...neither tainted by Earth's\Nhistory nor in need of arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.34,0:09:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies set an example for\Nall Earth's peaceful nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.68,0:10:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They set an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If only the people in space\Nhad heard that sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.12,0:10:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps they wouldn't\Nhave changed their minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.85,0:10:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not tell Mr. Peacecraft\Nabout the colonies' people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.19,0:10:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason we decided\Nto remain in space!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.13,0:10:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you stayed here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.76,0:10:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.56,0:10:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Alliance was\Ndefeated by OZ...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...our first thought was to\Nimmediately surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.60,0:10:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.77,0:10:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...surrendering would\Nleave space in great turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.51,0:10:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Space Colonies is\Na realm of precise calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, this management\Ncenter always supported...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.92,0:10:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...this colony's life zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.62,0:10:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The colony's rotation\Noperations...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...checking atmospheric\Nconditions...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.26,0:10:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,...and weather management.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.86,0:10:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Natural phenomena that are\Ntaken for granted on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.09,0:10:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,...are generated by machinery\Ncontrolled by people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.26,0:10:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,To live in this atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...people needed a new\Nawareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.27,0:10:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's insecurity...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.37,0:11:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you can completely\Nignore insecurity...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.71,0:11:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...you'll have difficulties\Nliving here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.31,0:11:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And insecure people feel\Nthe need for weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.85,0:11:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Because weapons give\Npeople a sense of security.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.15,0:11:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At what point can one\Nlose that sense of insecurity?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.79,0:11:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Men in space will attack Earth,\Nin their search for stable land.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.10,0:11:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an OZ mobile suit\Ntransport vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.43,0:11:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like they're finally\Ngoing to attack us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to be part of\Nyour counterattack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.67,0:11:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A goodwill ambassador mustn't\Nbe involved in a battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I switch between two identities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.44,0:11:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My experience in battle has\Ntaught me to be cunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.04,0:11:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.94,0:11:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.78,0:11:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.31,0:12:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Romefeller\NFoundation's plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.21,0:12:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,...to send space-manufactured\Nmobile dolls to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.69,0:12:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To resolve all disputes\Non Earth at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.46,0:12:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody comes to\Nthat conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.76,0:12:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't intend to send\Nmobile dolls to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.57,0:12:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Foundation's plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.23,0:12:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...will mean more\Nbloodshed on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.07,0:12:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The strong shall rule the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.74,0:12:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all we need\Nto attain peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.21,0:12:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But now His Excellency\Nhas refused his mission...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.51,0:12:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,...to rule the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.35,0:12:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,His Excellency?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.72,0:12:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,True public order will\Nnever be possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.25,0:12:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...unless His Excellency\Ncomes to outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.62,0:12:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in\Nmy staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.26,0:12:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Not true, Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.63,0:12:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You still have your duty\Nto serve as an OZ soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.97,0:12:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As an OZ soldier?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.70,0:12:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be doing him\Na favor by staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.77,0:12:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A soldier only needs to\Nfollow orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.64,0:13:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel, you're a leader who\Nstands above the soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.21,0:13:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But your superior abilities can\Nbe heightened as an OZ soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.61,0:13:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I implore you to serve as\Nan OZ soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.52,0:13:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to guide His Excellency,\Nbut to support him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.85,0:13:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As an OZ soldier to support\NMaster Treize...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.76,0:13:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what His Excellency\Ndesires.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.83,0:13:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Treize desires that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.90,0:13:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The mobile dolls have started\Na battle in the A Area...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.64,0:13:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,...of the Alliance Military Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.04,0:13:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be in range of Barge's\Nbeam cannon in 600 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.51,0:13:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What damage can we do\Nto the Alliance Colony?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.31,0:13:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can destroy their\Nelectrical power control...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,...and management facilities,\None shot should wipe it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.51,0:13:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.31,0:13:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Many civilians live there,\Nas well as military officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.52,0:13:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.89,0:13:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd know it's risky\Nliving in a military fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.86,0:13:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Colonel Une know\Nabout this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.66,0:13:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm acting on direct orders\Nfrom Duke Dermail!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.26,0:13:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We're to crush them and that\NOZ traitor, Zechs Merquise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.20,0:14:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get the Mercurius and\NVayeate ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.90,0:14:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, Trowa Barton!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.77,0:14:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go near the\Nmobile suit gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.57,0:14:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't trust traitors, whether\Nthey're enemies or allies!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.64,0:14:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une isn't aware\Nof this either?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.28,0:14:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Colonel has left for\Nthe battle against the Alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.55,0:14:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She left me in charge of\Noperations!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.49,0:14:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Restrain this man at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.36,0:14:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't overstep my boundaries\Nas an OZ soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.83,0:14:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have doubts\Nabout your plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.40,0:14:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...not to use the Vayeate\Nand the Mercurius...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.20,0:14:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,...to support the Colonel's\Ntroops.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:14:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A soldier doesn't need to\Nthink so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ideals about peace are for\Npeople in the top ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.47,0:14:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All we need to do is\Npursue victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.77,0:15:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Get closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.04,0:15:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Make up for reaction time\Nin close-range combat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.55,0:15:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.42,0:15:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.25,0:15:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We've lost 50% of our\NLeo troops!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.39,0:15:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We believe all the enemy\NTauruses are mobile dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.09,0:15:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,20% of our defense line\Nhas been destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.46,0:15:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Have the remaining civilians\Nin the colony been evacuated?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.36,0:15:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.36,0:15:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They left on our large shuttle\Nand are headed for safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.27,0:15:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, mobile dolls alone\Ncan't destroy this colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.04,0:15:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect that Barge will be\Nmaking the final blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.41,0:15:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This colony is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.11,0:15:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Grandfather?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.25,0:15:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first time a colony\Nhas been destroyed in war...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.68,0:15:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...since the colonies\Nwere built.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.55,0:16:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind needs to be shown\Nhow tragic the destruction is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.99,0:16:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of us who brought\Nmilitary power to space...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...and the colonies who are\Nconsidering it for themselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.70,0:16:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,...must remember this, so\Nthe wrong path won't be taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.17,0:16:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It hardly compensates for\Nwhat we've done...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.84,0:16:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...but I hope our deaths\Nsend the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.17,0:16:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to have dragged\Nyou into this, Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.04,0:16:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My thoughts exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.14,0:16:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Gwinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.53,0:16:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Barge's beam cannon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.97,0:16:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they seriously going to\Nwipe out the colony?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.74,0:17:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize is hoping we'll\Nput up a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.65,0:17:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you create a new future,\NTreize?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.72,0:17:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no choice left\Nbut to battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.09,0:17:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only way that remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Without fighting, nothing\Ncan be created.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.73,0:17:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.30,0:17:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.64,0:17:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Zechs Merquise...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.17,0:17:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or rather, my eternal friend,{\i0}\N{\i1}Milliardo Peacecraft.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.58,0:17:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm delighted to hear you've{\i0}\N{\i1}shown up in outer space.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.55,0:17:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ is changing, and I'm\Nsorely lacking in power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.65,0:17:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Romefeller's way, or rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,...the path that mankind is\Ntaking, is too selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.19,0:17:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I never expected their{\i0}\N{\i1}increased power...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.23,0:17:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...would lead them to{\i0}\N{\i1}abandon their compassion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.73,0:17:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to believe that OZ's\Nduty wasn't to take part in war.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.00,0:17:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But to educate soldiers\Nwho had the heart to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.77,0:18:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon battles will be\Nfought without people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.11,0:18:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm merely one soldier.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I chose of my own free will{\i0}\N{\i1}to resist that outcome.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.58,0:18:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Milliardo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.12,0:18:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have the power to alter\Nthe path chosen by Romefeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.99,0:18:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to speak with\Nsomeone who understands me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.79,0:18:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Milliardo, there's one other\Nperson who understands me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Her feelings toward me have\Ngiven her split personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.17,0:18:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Lady Une...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.67,0:18:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm making the person closest\Nto me feel insecure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.17,0:18:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got no right to\Ntalk about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.17,0:18:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I implore you, Milliardo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.48,0:18:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Please save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.96,0:18:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to fight for Treize...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.36,0:18:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,...to help realize his ideal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.13,0:19:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alliance Colony is\Nentering firing range.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.07,0:19:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire the beam cannon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.54,0:19:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But Colonel Une is still\Non the battlegrounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.21,0:19:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't matter;\Njust follow your orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.34,0:19:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Colonel knows the dangers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.75,0:19:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.56,0:19:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une would cancel any\Norders to attack the colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.57,0:19:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She's learned just how\Nfragile the colonies are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.51,0:19:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They missed it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.08,0:19:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that intentional?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.65,0:19:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Take me there...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.85,0:19:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Take me to Fortress Barge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.13,0:20:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel, you're safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.70,0:20:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.63,0:20:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichol.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.43,0:20:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to learn a great\Ndeal as a soldier today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.04,0:20:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Very informative.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.61,0:20:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And as your superior, I can't\Noverlook what you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.21,0:20:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.41,0:20:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The actions you took\Nwere justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.45,0:20:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I'm about\Nto do is also justified!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.96,0:20:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.09,0:20:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got no power.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.16,0:20:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In the confusion of\Nall these battles...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.40,0:20:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...I can only walk the\Npath of a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.37,0:20:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Romefeller Foundation\Ndecides to build...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.27,0:20:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...mobile doll manufacturing\Nfacilities on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.61,0:20:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The mass-produced mobile dolls\Nwill be used against Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.18,0:20:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The strategy is to send\Nthem to Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.82,0:20:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...and quickly resolve the\Nmany disputes on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.12,0:21:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,...by wiping out the opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.02,0:21:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,With these ultimate weapons...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.46,0:21:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,...the world heads for an age\Nwhere soldiers are redundant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.86,0:21:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Unidentified object headed\Nthis way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.80,0:21:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.30,0:21:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Gundam!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.20,0:21:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A Gundam has found us!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.07,0:21:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Assassinate the mobile dolls'\NChief Engineer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an easy mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Troops from the Lunar Base{\i0}\N{\i1}are headed for the Gundam!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.18,0:21:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no bullets, no fuel and\Nhardly any propulsive energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.75,0:21:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Chief Engineer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.95,0:21:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My life's in your hands!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.46,0:21:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Full retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.73,0:21:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.50,0:21:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.86,0:21:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundam doesn't have\Nthe power to retaliate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.67,0:21:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.14,0:21:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to take it to the\NLunar Base and check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.01,0:21:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Calling Lunar Base.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.24,0:21:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Stop your attack and{\i0}\N{\i1}capture the Gundam.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.71,0:21:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes, sir!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.65,0:22:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.68,0:22:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very kind of you,\NChief Engineer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.25,0:22:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nataku.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.25,0:22:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to become\Na lot stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.02,0:22:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear they have a factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.93,0:22:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they'll help us\Nget stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.17,0:23:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,People in outer space acquire\Nweapons to defend the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.57,0:23:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They do so under the pretext\Nof fearing an attack from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.31,0:23:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's OZ that manipulates\Ntheir fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.57,0:23:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To prevent mass-production\Nof mobile dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.01,0:23:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,...Duo heads to the moon\Nto destroy the Lunar Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.35,0:23:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,During the battle with Hilde,\Nthe colony volunteer soldier...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.55,0:23:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...Duo sees the chaotic\Nfuture of the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.05,0:23:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on Gundam Wing, Episode 23,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.22,0:23:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Duo, the God of Death Once Again".
